            <div type="note" subtype="biographical">
                <head type="title">Charles Smith &#x0026; Son, Cartographers</head>                
                
                <p>The manufacturer of Ruskin's celestial globe (17 cm x 88.9 mm, object GA2197, Southwark Heritage Centre and Walworth Library, London). 
                    Charles Smith (1768-1854) was appointed map seller to the Prince of Wales in 1809. 
                    The firm traded under the name Smith &#x0026; Son from 1826 to 1854, 
                    when it was taken over by Smith's son, William, and later his grandson, Guildford.
                </p>
            </div>
